Problem: EACCES: permission denied, mkdir '/bitnami/mariadb'
Solution for Arch-linux systems:
The solution was initially found here https://github.com/bitnami/bitnami-docker-mariadb/issues/136#issuecomment-354644226

1.Append 7cart/docker-compose.yml file with "fix-postgres-permissions" block like this:

version: '2'

services:
........
  fix-postgres-permissions:
    image: 'bitnami/postgresql:9.6'
    user: root
    command: chown -R 1001:1001 /bitnami
    volumes:
    - ./data/postgres:/bitnami
 
 2. Add "depends_on" clause inside "postgresql" block like this:
 
  postgresql:
  .....
      depends_on:
      - fix-postgres-permissions
